subject: Subpackage reorganization - devel-utils package
commitMessage:
Subpackage reorganization - devel-utils package

Utils subpackage has been renamed to devel-utils which now
includes additional binaries from base and -devel packages

Change-Id: Ib5cfa030921e067c1278db530045fec8412e7534
Signed-off-by: Jacek Bukarewicz <j.bukarewicz@samsung.com>

comments.message:
Patch Set 1: Verified+1

I've tested it on GBS on armv7l and i586 - it builds without errors.
I also flashed base image (around 60 packages) to the device - including modified glibc and it boots fine.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

(1 comment)

Generally looks okay; I can't think of any major issues here.

See my comment inline. I'm not sure if this issue is still relevant, but it's worth checking, IMO.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

Patch Set 1: -Verified

(3 comments)

As I wrote in comments - I'll merge tools-devel and devel packages together so devel package will also contain debugging tools.
I'll check usages of binaries which I put into glibc-tools in spec files to verify if anything needs to be done in other packages

Setting Verified to 0 for now
Uploaded patch set 2.

Patch Set 2:

[BUILD CHECK RESULT] This change is built against OBS project Tizen:IVI: 

 repository     arch           result         

 standard       i586           succeeded

Patch Set 2: Verified+1

I looked up usages of executables which I put previously to glibc-tools package. There are several usages of these. Building of such packages worked, but still I'd prefer to test it more which would take time. I would also rather do it on working and full ARM image which is not available currently - I could only test it on image with 69 packages.
For now I just moved several files to devel-utils package which are clearly just for debugging and I think it makes sense to move them there.
